WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Today we're going to understand the Fourier series.

2
00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:09.500
We start with a square wave, that flat signal that jumps between plus one and minus one.

3
00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:15.000
The remarkable claim is that this square wave is really a sum of simple sine waves.

4
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.000
We add the first harmonic, then the third, then the fifth, each a pure sine of higher frequency.

5
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:27.000
As we keep adding odd harmonics, the running sum gets closer and closer to the square wave.

6
00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:32.000
That convergence is the heart of Fourier analysis.
